r, white pepper and pork into it. Stir to coat pork with sauce and set aside to marinate for 10 minutes. Meanwhile, continue with recipe."},{"content":"Place oil, shiitake mushrooms and dried shrimp (if using) in mixing bowl and sauté <b>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add marinated pork along with marinade and stir-fry <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add drained rice and stir-fry <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>, then transfer mixture to 10 metal moulds (Ø 5 cm, height 5 cm). Place filled moulds in Varoma dish."},{"content":"Place water in mixing bowl, set Varoma in position and steam <b>40 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma and unmould rice puddings. Garnish with chopped coriander and chopped roasted peanuts and serve hot with sweet chilli sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<i>Rice tube puddings are a popular snack at Taiwanese night markets. If you remember to soak the rice ahead of time, you can prepare this recipe quickly at home, thanks to your Thermomix.<\/i>","If using long-grain rice, soak longer: at least <b>3 hours<b> or overnight in fridge.<br>- Dried shrimp are available in Asian supermarkets. You can omit them or replace with shallots, for a different but pleasant result.<br>- Use metal moulds such as dariole moulds. You can also use <b>7 heat-resistant<b> drinking glasses <b>(Ø 7 cm,<b> <b>6 cm height).<b> In this case, increase water to <b>900 g<b> and steaming time to <b>50-55 minutes.<b> If your moulds or glasses are a different size than specified, you may need to adjust the steaming time."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","2h 30m","10 cups"]}